column1: #Text=NASA 's InSight Lander makes it to Mars
#Text=On Monday shortly before noon US west coast time ( 2000 UTC ) , NASA 's InSight lander successfully touched down on Elysium Planitia on Mars .
#Text=It sent a signal beep and image of the surface of Mars to the Jet Propulsion Laboratory in California .
#Text=Artist 's rendition of the InSight Lander showing the solar panels in their open position after landing , heat flow instrument in the deployed position , and seismometer .
#Text=The lander used aerobraking with a heat shield , then a parachute and finally rockets to achieve a soft landing on the surface .
#Text=It used similar entry , descent , and landing sequence to the Phoenix spacecraft .

#Text=Insight project manager Tom Hoffman said , " We hit the Martian atmosphere at 12,300 mph [ miles per hour ; 19,800 kilometres per hour ] , and the whole sequence to touching down on the surface took only [ six and a half ] minutes [ ... ]
